== Welcome to Freescape! ==

You're about to enter a persistent world that's shaped by your actions and the actions of other players. Please take a moment to read the following to learn more about the server.

Discord: https://discord.gg/q38r3gw


== Skills & Leveling ==

Freescape does not use any classes from vanilla NWN. Instead, character progression is in the form of skills and perks. In general, if you want to get better at something you simply need to practice it.

Want to be a warrior? Equip a sword and shield and start fighting enemies. Want to be a farmer? Get a shovel and tools and start caring for your crops. Or if you want, do a little bit of everything and be a jack-of-all-trades.

Your experience on Freescape is entirely defined by what you choose to do and your individual play style.


== Perks ==

Perks are upgrades for your character that are purchased with SP. You earn 1 SP every time you raise a skill level.

In your rest menu, you'll find an option for "View Perks". Click this to enter the Perks menu. From here you can purchase perks or view the ones you've already bought.

There are only a handful of Perks to choose from in the beginning. As you level up your skills, more options will be unlocked.


== Construction ==

Construction is the act of building objects like tables, chairs, crafting devices, and eventually even entire buildings. 

You'll start by using the "Structure Tool" which is in your inventory. Simply pick a location that hasn't been claimed by another player and create a construction site. It will appear at the location you chose.

Use the construction site to select a blueprint. Only territory flags will initially be available. These are used to claim the surrounding area and they dictate how many of each structure type can be built within its influence.

Once you've picked a blueprint you will need to acquire items like wood, stone, and other resources. Once you have these in your inventory equip a hammer and start "bashing" the construction site. Resources will be removed from your inventory as you build.

After you've built the territory flag, you repeat the same process again to make other objects. Keep in mind that you may need to buy a Perk first before the blueprints will show up on the construction site menu.

Everything you build is completely persistent. You don't need to worry about it disappearing after a server reset. This goes for any containers you build as well.


== Crafting ==

Crafting is a core concept in Freescape. Nearly everything can be either constructed or found in the game world. If you choose not to become a crafter - make sure you make friends with one!

Each crafting skill works a little differently. In general, you will build a crafting device (see the "Construction" section) and then you'll gather materials needed to make items.

Make sure you purchase the necessary Perk before you start making items. Otherwise you won't find any blueprints to select in the crafting menu!

After selecting a blueprint you will place the necessary resources inside the device. If the blueprint requires tools, be sure to put those inside the device as well. After this is done simply take the "Craft Item" object inside of the container to start crafting.

Depending on your skill level and the difficulty of the blueprint you will either succeed or fail to make the item. If you fail, a small number of components may be lost. So be careful and choose blueprints you have the skill to make!


== Magic & Abilities ==

Magic and abilities can be learned by buying the appropriate Perk (see the "Perks" section). After you buy the perk, an item will appear in your inventory. Any time you want to cast the spell you simply need to use the item and select a target.

All magic and many abilities require you to expend "mana" every time you use them. This is a resource that regenerates automatically over time. There are also abilities and items which will restore mana when used.

There are a handful of magic schools. 

Evocation - Generally offensive magic which deals damage.
Alteration - Generally defensive and recovery magic.
Summoning - Generally focused on calling creatures to do your bidding.

You're free to mix and match magic skills as you like. Keep in mind that heavy armor will double your casting time for all spells, though.


== Farming ==

Living off the land is a huge deal in Freescape. Since there are no NPC stores you will be expected to find and grow your own resources to survive.

Farming is performed by making a Shovel and using it on a target location. You can do this anywhere farming is allowed - you do not need to own a territory. However, it's a good idea to have a way to protect the crops as other players can freely forage through them once fully grown.

After you've dug a hole, click it and choose to "plant a seed". Once the container pops up you simply need to drag and drop the seed inside to plant it.

Plants take several hours to fully grow. You will need to periodically check on them to make sure they're growing properly. Be sure you water them!

There's no way for plants to die, but if you do not properly take care of them it will take much longer for them to mature. You will also miss out on potential bonuses that you would have gotten otherwise.


== Weapon Classes ==

Freescape uses several custom categories for weapons. They are as follows:

**One Handed Weapon Classes**

Blades - Bastard Sword, Longsword, Katana, Scimitar, Battleaxe

Finesse Blades - Dagger, Rapier, Short Sword, Kukri, Sickle, Whip, One-Handed Axe

Blunts - Club, Light Flail, Light Hammer, Mace, Morningstar


**Two-Handed Weapon Classes**

Heavy Blades - Greataxe, Greatsword, Dwarven Waraxe

Heavy Blunts - Heavy Flail, Warhammer, Dire Mace, Quarterstaff

Polearms - Halberd, Scyte, Spear, Trident


**Twin Blades Weapon Classes**

Twin Blades - Double Axe, Two-Bladed Sword


** Martial Arts Weapon Classes**

Martial Arts - Unarmed, Power Glove, Kama


**Archery Weapon Classes**

Bows - Longbow, Shortbow

Crossbows - Heavy Crossbow, Light Crossbow


**Throwing Weapon Classes**

Throwing Weapons - Sling, Dart, Shuriken, Throwing Axe


== Conclusion ==

We want to welcome you again to Freescape and hope you enjoy yourself! If you have any questions or concerns be sure to contact us on Discord.
